SIMPLE: polynomial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polynomial
<hw>Pol`y*no"mi*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + <ets>-nomial</ets>, as in <ets>monomial</ets>,
<ets>binomial</ets>: cf. F. <ets>polyn⟦ocir⟧me</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Alg.)</fld> <def>An expression composed of two or more terms,
connected by the signs <it>plus</it> or <it>minus</it>; as,
<mathex>a<exp>2</exp> - 2ab + b<exp>2</exp></mathex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polynomial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Polynomial
<hw>Pol`y*no"mi*al</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Containing many
names or terms; multinominal; <as>as, the <ex>polynomial</ex>
theorem</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting of two or more words; having names
consisting of two or more words; <as>as, a <ex>polynomial</ex> name;
<ex>polynomial</ex> nomenclature.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polynuclear</ent>⟦br⟧
